            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText"></span>                    
            Amid all of the happiness and joy that we find living on the earth, we also find that we have some adversity. We had this in our family when Kenneth was diagnosed with Alzheimer’s disease. He was around 80 years old and he was in the midst of this for seven years. It was quite a challenge for the whole family. I was at home with him alone. Our children were all gone, of course, so we faced this challenge together. At first it was total loss of episodes of different things in his memory.  <br />
            </span>

