                    <li><%= link_to image_tag("carma/icandohard/small/Kennethsphysicaldecline1a.png", :class => "fboxImageSize"), "https://dqp5htr9jmxmj.cloudfront.net/assets/carma/icandohard/large/Kennethsphysicaldecline1.jpg", :class => "fancybox", :rel => "gallery4", :title => "" %>
                    </li>
                    <!--li><%#= link_to image_tag("carma/icandohard/small/Kennethsphysicaldecline2.png", :class => "fboxImageSize"), "https://dqp5htr9jmxmj.cloudfront.net/assets/carma/icandohard/large/Kennethsphysicaldecline2.jpg", :class => "fancybox", :rel => "gallery4", :title => "" %>
                    </li-->
                    <li><%= link_to image_tag("carma/icandohard/small/Kennethsphysicaldecline3.png", :class => "fboxImageSize"), "https://dqp5htr9jmxmj.cloudfront.net/assets/carma/icandohard/large/Kennethsphysicaldecline3.jpg", :class => "fancybox", :rel => "gallery4", :title => "" %>
                    </li>
                </ol>    
            </div>
            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    The first indication we had was when he ran into a neighbor’s mailbox with a car and came back home and did not even realize what he had done. We went to the doctor to get some help and discovered that he had had some mini strokes. They weren’t quite sure what the future would hold, but they anticipated that he was having a form of dementia. 
 
            </span>

            <span id="SEE_MORE"><a href="#" id="restofstory6-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory6');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
            </span>

            <div id="restofstory6" class="more">
                <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    We began with seven years of his going through the process of Alzheimer’s disease. We had a great deal of help from the family. The trauma of seeing him digress was difficult. He always was trying to get back to the farm where he lived early on.<br /><br />

                    I had a great deal of help. I had to depend on family help, as well as neighbors. I learned that many times we must accept help. Heavenly Father expects us to serve each other and to help each other, and I learned through these experiences while Kenneth was experiencing all this that we need to love and support each other. My family has certainly done that. We came together as a family, did all that we could for him, provided service to help him in any way that was needed, and we certainly enjoyed many blessings with that.<br /><br />

                    As I look back on that period of time, I know that my faith in Heavenly Father was strengthened. I came to realize that how we respond to adversity and how we get through it helps strengthen our testimonies and our faith in Heavenly Father and what the future will be, if we are able to keep faithful and help each other the very best that we can.<br /><br />

                    It was difficult to watch him regress. There was a period of time right toward the end when he did not know who I was at all, and that was difficult.<br /><br />

                    For seven years he struggled to find himself and struggled to get back to his home; the farm was where he was always trying to go. We had to watch carefully because he was wanting to leave. He passed away on July the 25th in 2003. We were sorry to lose him, but we felt it was time for him to go.

                </span>
